<p>"Ineffable, yet deeply tangible", my thoughts exactly, Jackx. It's the most curious thing, and feeds both doubt and certainty in me.</p><p>Thumbs up to Jesus, too, except we don't need to seek the Kingdom anymore, we are in it already. I think those Christians got it right in the sense the whole thing is quite easy to solve, or has been solved already. Death ( fear ) has been conquered. It never had any basis. And then you're reborn ( recovery ). It's interesting how the Christian belief comes to make new sense after this, as a somewhat clumsy attempt to grasp what's going on. And many other teachings besides.</p>
